  "genie_instructions": "ALWAYS prefer metric views with MEASURE() syntax for aggregation questions. The sensor_readings_metrics view (source: sensor_readings) has dimensions: reading_date, equipment_id, equipment_type, field_name, alert_level. Measures: avg_health_score, min_rul_days, alarm_trip_count, total_readings. The maintenance_events_metrics view (source: maintenance_events) has dimensions: event_date, equipment_id, equipment_type, field_name, event_type, was_predicted. Measures: total_events, total_downtime_hours, total_repair_cost_usd, total_production_loss_bbl. Use GROUP BY ALL with MEASURE() queries. Only query base tables directly when the question requires columns not available as metric view dimensions (e.g. equipment_name).",
